"{\"uid\": \"newseu.cgtn.com-news-2024-09-08-Are-the-Olympics-too-Western--1wGs2kiMbXG-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Marillier in London  Copied  EXPLAINER VIDEO: India, Egypt among contenders for 2036 Games  Paris took a bow on Sunday, after hosting both the Olympics and Paralympics over the last six weeks.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 405, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999998888338331, \"rank\": 1.035427921141767e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 259, \"end\": 264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9629734132531697, \"rank\": 0.03844943418197902, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9837146041824363, \"rank\": 0.016554984132933215, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990764081, \"rank\": 9.236738730486889e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next Games will go to Los Angeles in the United States.\", \"from\": 407, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9989823849976406, \"rank\": 0.0010176721702982372, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 452, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999995820490731, \"rank\": 3.5802172546027065e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be a record fifth Olympics on U.S. soil.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will also be the third time that LA has played host.\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian city of Brisbane will take the baton in 2032.\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0173257365715192e-16, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 595, \"end\": 603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9887738201827724, \"rank\": 0.011343942855379097, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia has already hosted two Games - first in 1956 and again in 2000.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999665566082456, \"rank\": 1.848800224308296e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, India is still on the sidelines, even though it has the world's biggest population.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9629734132531697, \"rank\": 0.03844943418197902, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Likewise, Africa has 1.5 billion people, yet no African country has hosted the Games.\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 888, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is the fourth European city to host the Olympics and Paralympics in 32 years.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 890, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990764081, \"rank\": 9.236738730486889e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  Will 2036 be a turning point?\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1009, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This does not necessarily mean the International Olympic Committee (IOC) is biased.\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has to select host cities that can enhance the Olympic and Paralympic brands.\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0232861850195722e-22, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some developing countries simply do not have the funds and infrastructure to host global sports events.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Western nations have organized eight of the last 10 Games - Beijing 2008 and Rio 2016 being the only exceptions.\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has said that inclusivity is a key part of its mission, adding 'together' to the famous Olympic motto, 'faster, higher, stronger' in 2021.\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1407, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0232861850195722e-22, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, will things change in 2036?\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1581, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Egypt announced in August that it would bid for those Games.\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9837146041824363, \"rank\": 0.016554984132933215, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The north African nation opened a stadium around 50 kilometers from Cairo this year.\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairo\", \"score\": 0.9999999991146069, \"rank\": 8.737847047031901e-10, \"text\": \"Cairo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's indicated that it may build another 20 facilities that could be used for major sports events.\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, India is edging closer to a bid.\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9629734132531697, \"rank\": 0.03844943418197902, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Prime Minister Narendra Modi said last year that his country would aim to host in 2036.\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1888, \"end\": 1901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Narendra Modi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"India has some experience with sporting spectacles, hosting the annual IPL cricket tournament as well as the Commonwealth Games in 2010.\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1961, \"end\": 1966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9629734132531697, \"rank\": 0.03844943418197902, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Egypt opened a 93,000-seat stadium in its Olympic City complex earlier this year.\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2099, \"end\": 2104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9837146041824363, \"rank\": 0.016554984132933215, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  The race to make history  But there are other countries that may be hoping to make some history of their own.\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Muslim-majority country has never hosted the Olympics; neither has a state in the Middle East.\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2299, \"end\": 2322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslim_world\", \"score\": 0.9845587487270004, \"rank\": 0.015683422947383844, \"text\": \"Muslim-majority country\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslim_world\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslim_world\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Qatar bid for the 2032 event, but lost out to Brisbane in Australia.\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2394, \"end\": 2399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999915071900004, \"rank\": 8.49240882915456e-06, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}, {\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9887738201827724, \"rank\": 0.011343942855379097, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}, {\"begin\": 2452, \"end\": 2461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999665566082456, \"rank\": 1.848800224308296e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It hosted the FIFA World Cup two years ago and reports suggest it may try to capitalize on that success with a bid for the 2036 Games.\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indonesia has the world's biggest Muslim population and is now building its new capital, Nusantara.\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2599, \"end\": 2608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.999994080459841, \"rank\": 5.915097951070518e-06, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}, {\"begin\": 2633, \"end\": 2639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"score\": 0.9668170099579314, \"rank\": 0.03260992990767244, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muslims\"}, {\"begin\": 2688, \"end\": 2697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_Aerospace\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.630977072277445e-14, \"text\": \"Nusantara\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_Aerospace\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesian_Aerospace\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not clear if the country's government will bid for the 2036 event, but Indonesian officials met with IOC President Thomas Bach last month.\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2775, \"end\": 2785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.999912321067811, \"rank\": 8.748550553428427e-05, \"text\": \"Indonesian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IOC President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2819, \"end\": 2830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"State-owned Enterprises Minister Erick Thohir posted on social media, saying \\\"Indonesia has the potential to host international sporting events, including the Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2876, \"end\": 2888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erick_Thohir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Erick Thohir\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erick_Thohir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erick_Thohir\"}, {\"begin\": 2921, \"end\": 2930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.999994080459841, \"rank\": 5.915097951070518e-06, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"T\\u00c3\\u00bcrkiye may be another contender.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's positioned at the crossroads of Europe and Asia, placing it in a useful timezone for TV networks looking to maximize viewership on both continents.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also getting ready to test its mettle in a major event, the 2027 European Games.\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Qatar may be a contender for the 2036 Olympics after becoming the first Middle Eastern state to host the FIFA World Cup.\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3289, \"end\": 3294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999915071900004, \"rank\": 8.49240882915456e-06, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}, {\"begin\": 3361, \"end\": 3375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\", \"score\": 0.9999999997744453, \"rank\": 2.2127898292530143e-10, \"text\": \"Middle Eastern\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Middle_East\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  The modern Olympics will be 140 years old when the 2036 Games begin.\", \"from\": 3410, \"to\": 3484, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has not said when it will name the host city.\", \"from\": 3485, \"to\": 3538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3489, \"end\": 3492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0232861850195722e-22, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris got the nod seven years before the 2024 Games began, while Brisbane had 11 years' notice.\", \"from\": 3539, \"to\": 3634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3539, \"end\": 3544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990764081, \"rank\": 9.236738730486889e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3604, \"end\": 3612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9887738201827724, \"rank\": 0.011343942855379097, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But whenever the announcement comes, some countries will argue it's not a moment too soon.\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe toStoryboard: A weekly newsletterbringing you the best of CGTN every Friday  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 3728, \"to\": 4075, \"entities\": []}]}"